### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@uploadDir = uploads

### Upload a single valid file
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary

------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="files"; filename="test.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./test-files/test.jpg
------WebKitFormBoundary--

### Upload multiple valid files
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary

------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="files"; filename="test1.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./test-files/test1.jpg
------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="files"; filename="test2.png"
Content-Type: image/png

< ./test-files/test2.png
------WebKitFormBoundary--

### Try to upload an invalid file type
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary

------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="files"; filename="test.exe"
Content-Type: application/x-msdownload

< ./test-files/test.exe
------WebKitFormBoundary--

### Try to upload an empty file
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary

------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="files"; filename="empty.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

------WebKitFormBoundary--

### List all uploaded files
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files

### Download a specific file
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files/{{filename}}

### Try to download a non-existent file
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files/non-existent-file.txt 